Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: "AccessDenied" when listing roles

Verify your AWS credentials are configured correctly
Check that your user/role has iam:ListRoles permission
Ensure you're using the correct AWS region
Issue: Cannot assume any roles

Verify the trust policy allows your principal
Check for required Condition statements (ExternalId, MFA)
Ensure role ARN format is correct
Issue: Scripts fail with "NoCredentialsError"

Run aws configure list to verify credentials
Check environment variables: AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID, AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
Ensure boto3 can find credentials in ~/.aws/credentials
Issue: Rate limiting errors

Add delays between API calls (time.sleep(1))
Implement exponential backoff for retries
Reduce parallelization in automation scripts
